statement:
Circle \emph{all} of the following statements that are true for all
invertible matrices \emph{A}, and all matrices \emph{B} and \emph{C} of
the same size as \emph{A} and all scalars \emph{r} ≠ 0:

\begin{enumerate}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  (AB)C = A(BC)
\item
  (A+B)(A-B) = A\textsuperscript{2}-B\textsuperscript{2}
\item
  A\textsuperscript{T}B\textsuperscript{T} = (AB)\textsuperscript{T}
\item
  (A\textsuperscript{-1})\textsuperscript{T} =
  (A\textsuperscript{T})\textsuperscript{-1}
\item
  (rA)\textsuperscript{-1} = $\frac1{r}$A\textsuperscript{-1}
\end{enumerate}
